Class SemanticVersion

  • java.lang.Object
    • info.augendre.perm_maker.versioning.SemanticVersion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<SemanticVersion>

    public class SemanticVersion
extends Object
implements Comparable<SemanticVersion>
    This class aims to compare semantic version numbers. Semantic version numbers are defined here : http://semver.org

    gaugendre

      • SemanticVersion

        public SemanticVersion(String version)
        Constructs a SemanticVersion from a String.
        Parameters:
        version - The version number.

        Must be in the following format : "X.Y.Z-PRE.W", where :

        • X is the major version number
        • Y is the minor version number
        • Z is the patch version number
        • PRE is the pre-release tag (see PreRelease)
        • W is the pre-release version number

      • normalize

        public static String normalize(String versionNumber)
        Removes the "v" that may be the first character of a version number.

        Examples : 

             normalize("v1.0.4") returns "1.0.4"
     normalize("1.0.4") returns "1.0.4"
        Parameters:
        versionNumber - The version number in String format.
        Returns:
        The normalized version number in String format.
